# Comprehensive Report on Strategies to Reduce Air Pollution

## Introduction

Air pollution remains one of the most pressing environmental and public health challenges worldwide. According to the World Health Organization, nine out of ten people globally breathe polluted air, leading to premature deaths, increased disease burden, and economic losses ([C40 Cities, n.d.](https://www.c40.org/other/clean-air-cities-declaration)). The sources of air pollution are multifaceted, ranging from vehicular emissions, industrial activities, household energy use, to agricultural practices. Effective reduction of air pollution requires coordinated efforts from individuals, enterprises, and governments, employing a combination of behavioral changes, technological advancements, policy interventions, and urban planning.

This report synthesizes current knowledge and actionable strategies to reduce air pollution, drawing from authoritative sources including the Clean Air Cities Declaration by C40, the United Nations Environment Programme, the UK’s National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE), and peer-reviewed scientific literature. The report aims to provide a detailed, evidence-based, and structured overview of practical measures applicable at various levels of society.

