## 2. Enterprise and Industrial Sector Strategies

### 2.1 Industrial Emission Controls

Industries are significant sources of pollutants such as particulate matter, nitrogen oxides, and sulfur dioxide.

- **Advanced Emission Standards:** Implementing stricter emission controls and end-of-pipe technologies (e.g., scrubbers, catalytic converters) reduces industrial pollution ([UN Environment, 2018](https://wedocs.unep.org/handle/20.500.11822/25496)).

- **Energy Efficiency:** Upgrading to energy-efficient processes and equipment lowers fuel consumption and emissions ([Sofia et al., 2020](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11356-020-08647-x)).

- **Renewable Energy Adoption:** Shifting to biomass, solar, wind, or hydro power in industrial energy supply reduces reliance on fossil fuels ([Sofia et al., 2020](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11356-020-08647-x)).

### 2.2 Agricultural Practices

Agriculture contributes to ammonia and methane emissions, precursors to particulate matter.

- **Livestock Management:** Improving manure storage, frequent removal, and anaerobic digestion reduce emissions ([UN Environment, 2018](https://wedocs.unep.org/handle/20.500.11822/25496)).

- **Fertilizer Use:** Efficient application and use of inhibitors reduce nitrogenous emissions ([UN Environment, 2018](https://wedocs.unep.org/handle/20.500.11822/25496)).

- **Dietary Shifts:** Reducing consumption of animal products lowers agricultural emissions ([Sofia et al., 2020](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11356-020-08647-x)).

### 2.3 Shipping Sector

- **Fuel Quality Regulation:** Mandating low-sulfur fuels and speed reductions decrease shipping emissions ([UN Environment, 2018](https://wedocs.unep.org/handle/20.500.11822/25496)).

- **Dock Electrification:** Using shore-side power for docked vessels avoids emissions from idling engines ([Sofia et al., 2020](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11356-020-08647-x)).

